The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 The City Diary

 A fire broke out in the room of fisheries minister Kiranmoy Nanda at Writers? Buildings on Monday evening, prompting the minister to vacate the chamber in a hurry. Officials said smoke was seen coming out from an air-conditioner in the minister?s chamber at 6.30 pm. Nanda was then in the middle of a meeting with his officials. Fire brigade officials at the secretariat rushed to the room and doused the fire. This was the second incident of a fire in the minister?s room. 

 State commerce and industries minster Nirupam Sen will leave for Italy on Wednesday to participate in Asia Week, to be held in Milan between September 24 and October 3. The minister will be accompanied by industries secretary Nirupam Sen and West Bengal Industrial Development Corporation managing director Gopal Krishna. Participants from Bengal have been allotted 3,500 sq-ft space to exhibit their wares, ranging from jewellery to jute items. The event is being organised by the Indo-Italian Chamber of Commerce.

 P.V. George, national president of the Indian Medical Association (IMA), met chief minister Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee on Monday to plead for two arrested doctors of Baranagar. Deb Narayan Sur and Anima Dasgupta were arrested from Rogmukti Nursing Home on September 8 after a patient, who was to be operated upon by the duo, died before surgery. ?The chief minister assured us that action would be taken against the police for arresting the doctors even before a medical board could pronounce them guilty. The doctors are yet to be chargesheeted,? George said.

 A 60-year-old unidentified man died on Monday after a private bus knocked him down at the Raja Dinendra Street- Gas Street intersection. Police said the bus on route 12C/1 hit the victim from behind. He was taken to NRS Hospital, where he died. The bus driver was arrested. 

 Police are looking for a person who had allegedly misbehaved with a five-year-old girl in Duttabad, Salt Lake. Sources said the 45-year-old had fled the area after the incident on Monday. Officials said no evidence of rape could be found during medical examination of the girl. A complaint of misbehaviour has been lodged with police. 

 Bapan Chowdhury, a resident of Subhasgram, was arrested on Monday in connection with the reported abduction of a local girl. Superintendent of police (South 24-Parganas) S.N. Gupta said the girl and Chowdhury were missing for the past seven days. Chowdhury returned on Monday, but failed to disclose the whereabouts of the girl. He, however, told the police that he had spotted another girl of the locality in a red-light area of Patna. 

 Director of medical education C.R. Maiti advised diabetic patients to take a balanced diet, rather than medicines. He also cautioned them against performing exercises without consulting a doctor. Maiti was inaugurating a seminar on Sunday on ?Diabetes Detection and Education Programme?, in association with the Diabetic Association of India. 

 Sudhangshu Mura, 22, was admitted to SSKM Hospital early on Monday after he was knocked down by a private bus on Diamond Harbour Road. 

